{"id":14881576,"mediaExerciseId":"a6f82835-1d83-4c95-8a0e-3e63298d5126","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"16","chapterTitle":"Financial Leverage and Capital Structure Policy","groupId":612419,"groupTitle":"Excel Master IT! Problem","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":572,"solutions":[{"id":6443018,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine how the real estate company can maximize their total market value by choosing whether they issue debt or equity. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The total market value of a company is measured by the total debt and equity they issued to finance their assets. Although debt and equity can function the same way by financing the assets or other investments of the company, the company should choose to issue debt to finance their investment. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"By using debt, they can declare it for tax deduction. This is good for them short term since the investment will still be funded but the tax they will pay will become lower due to the tax deduction. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3cc1227d-3e04-47b8-84a4-39f62671dbe4","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Editio